sys_documentation.hint: This is the period during which the cooldown doesn't apply immediately following an upload. This allows many uploads to stack up and send in quick sequence before engaging the cooldown. (This should always be LESS than the minimum possible return time.)
sys_documentation.label: grace_period_cooldown_seconds
sys_documentation.name: var__m_sys_hub_flow_input_f703031f1bf1d4104ca7edf9bc4bcbb2

sys_documentation.hint: Specify the number of MACs that have to appear across all devices before a MAC is considered "virtual" (i.e. not a real MAC that can be matched) and disqualified from the matching algorithm that attempts to pick a MAC to be linked to Armis.
sys_documentation.label: virtual_adapter_mac_count_threshold
sys_documentation.name: var__m_sys_hub_flow_input_f703031f1bf1d4104ca7edf9bc4bcbb2

sys_documentation.hint: Specify the text on the tag that will always be pushed up to Armis when an upload occurs.

sys_documentation.hint: Specify the API secret provided by the Armis service account configured for admin access to Armis

sys_documentation.hint: The maximum number of iterations that can be performed by MAIN_ProcessQueue. This way, if a certain operation fails to close out correctly (which it shouldn't but you never know), it won't max out the CPU attempting to run the operation over and over.

sys_documentation.hint: An integer from 1 to 100 that represents the percentage of time that the integration is allowed to run. Note that API time is included, and this time does not occupy the CPU. (e.g. "50" means that 50% of every minute can be utilized by this integration.)
